  "topic": "Hydrocarbons",
  "question": "What is an alkyne?",
  "options": {
    "A": "Hydrocarbon with double bonds",
    "B": "Hydrocarbon with triple bonds",
    "C": "Saturated hydrocarbon",
    "D": "Aromatic compound"
  },
  "answer": "B",
  "explanation": "Alkynes (C\u2099H\u2082\u2099\u208b\u2082) contain C\u2261C triple bonds. Examples: ethyne (acetylene), propyne."
